# Continuum configuration — copy to .env (all optional; runs with none).

# ============================================================================
# WHY AN LLM KEY?  Continuum turns a raw conversation into STRUCTURED reasoning
# (decisions + why, rejected alternatives + why, hypotheses, open questions).
# That extraction is an LLM job. Two independent LLM uses:
#   1) Continuum's own extractor  → needs OPENAI_API_KEY / ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#      below. WITHOUT a key it still works, but in rough "heuristic" mode (regex).
#   2) Cognee's side (knowledge graph + embeddings/semantic search):
#      - backend=cognee (local SDK)  → uses YOUR OpenAI key (same one below).
#      - backend=cognee_cloud (hosted) → Cognee runs the LLM+embeddings for you,
#        so NO OpenAI key is needed for the Cognee side.
# So on cognee_cloud you can run with just the Cognee key; add an OpenAI/Anthropic
# key only if you also want clean (non-heuristic) reasoning extraction.
# ============================================================================

# --- LLM extraction for the REASONING layer (clean vs heuristic) ---
# Any OpenAI-compatible endpoint:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# ...or Anthropic:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5

# --- storage backend ---
# CONTINUUM_BACKEND=local          # local | cognee | cognee_cloud
# CONTINUUM_HOME=~/.continuum      # data dir
# CONTINUUM_DATASET=continuum
# CONTINUUM_RESUME_BUDGET=8000     # max tokens in a resume package

# --- Cognee Cloud (hosted platform = the COMPLETE superset: ingest + knowledge
#     graph + semantic retrieval, managed LLM). Get these from the Cognee platform. ---
# CONTINUUM_BACKEND=cognee_cloud
# COGNEE_API_URL=https://tenant-XXXXXXXX.aws.cognee.ai
# COGNEE_API_KEY=your-cognee-platform-key
# (COGNEE_TENANT_ID / COGNEE_USER_ID are shown by the platform; not required by Continuum today.)
